{"id":73922,"title":"A rare case of limbic encephalitis with anti leucine-rich glioma inactivated-1 (LGI1) antibodies.","abstract":"We report a case of limbic encephalitis with LGI1 antibodies and cranial MRI abnormality. A 41-year-old woman who presented with confusional state that had started 1 month ago. Brain magnetic resonance imaging revealed hyperintense signal in right basal ganglia followed by hyperintense signals in left hippocampus and bilateral basal ganglia half a month later. This case expands the spectrum of limbic encephalitis to include LGI1 antibodies and cranial MRI changing process. ","date":"2014-07-07","categories":"Neoplasms","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24878970","annotations":[{"name":"Hippocampus","weight":0.889548,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hippocampus"},{"name":"Basal ganglia","weight":0.848983,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Basal_ganglia"},{"name":"Magnetic resonance imaging","weight":0.832513,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Magnetic_resonance_imaging"},{"name":"Brain","weight":0.710232,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brain"},{"name":"Medical imaging","weight":0.710232,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medical_imaging"},{"name":"Antibody","weight":0.664199,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antibody"},{"name":"Glioma","weight":0.487406,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glioma"},{"name":"Ganglion","weight":0.406572,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ganglion"},{"name":"Human skull","weight":0.351494,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_skull"},{"name":"Encephalitis","weight":0.241348,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Encephalitis"},{"name":"Resonance","weight":0.147927,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Resonance"},{"name":"Magnetism","weight":0.134742,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Magnetism"},{"name":"L